          "merged_at": null
        },
        "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nThis PR improves performance and clarity in the Markdown-It integration by preventing all languages from being loaded by default.\r\n\r\nPreviously, the “Getting Started” example automatically loaded **every available language**, which caused slow startup times and poor performance.\r\n\r\nThis PR introduces the following changes:\r\n\r\n- The example now loads **only necessary languages** explicitly.\r\n- A **warning message** is displayed when all languages are being loaded, informing users of:\r\n  - The **number of languages** being loaded,\r\n  - A recommendation to load only required languages,\r\n  - An example showing how to configure language loading properly.\r\n- Users can disable warnings using `warnings: false` in the options.\r\n\r\nThese updates help users avoid performance issues and understand how to load languages efficiently.\r\n\r\n### Linked Issues\r\n\r\nfixes #853\r\n\r\n",
